the ocean's

19:36.509 --> 19:41.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wildlife; and restoring federal
education
grants for prisoners.

19:41.580 --> 19:48.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: Today on Capitol
Hill, a Senate
hearing looked into ending the
practice overseas

19:48.120 --> 19:49.922 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of child marriage.

19:49.955 --> 19:54.994 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But what wasn't examined
thousands of American
girls and women here in the
United States

19:55.027 --> 19:58.164 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who are forced into marriage
every year.

19:58.197 --> 20:02.868 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the first of two parts,
special correspondent
Gayle Tzemach Lemmon reports.

20:02.902 --> 20:08.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: For Nina
Van Harn, raising
her children today is a radical
departure

20:08.974 --> 20:10.609 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from her own upbringing.

20:10.643 --> 20:14.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN, Michigan: My
childhood was
part magical, and part
complicated.

20:14.447 --> 20:18.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: She was
raised in rural
Michigan on a 40-acre farm in a
tight-knit

20:18.984 --> 20:23.656 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
community that practiced a
conservative form
of evangelical Christianity.

20:23.689 --> 20:28.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Its members largely kept to
themselves, more
"Little House on the Prairie"
than modern-day

20:28.561 --> 20:29.795 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
America.

20:29.829 --> 20:33.332 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Growing up, she always knew one
day was coming.

20:33.365 --> 20:35.568 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She recorded its arrival in her
diary.

20:35.601 --> 20:39.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN: "Dear Kit (ph)"
-- that was
the name of the girl in the
journal -- "You

20:39.438 --> 20:41.507 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
will never guess what happened
today.

20:41.540 --> 20:45.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This morning after breakfast,
papa sat Naomi
(ph) and I down at the kitchen
table and nailed

20:45.377 --> 20:47.413 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
us both with a load of bricks.

20:47.446 --> 20:49.381 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He believes he found husbands
for both of
us."

20:49.415 --> 20:51.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Van Harn
had turned
19.

20:52.017 --> 20:53.786 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She was legally an adult.

20:53.819 --> 20:57.656 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was no gun to her head, no
chains around
her wrists.

20:57.690 --> 21:02.761 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But because of lifelong
pressures from her
family and her upbringing, she
considers herself

21:02.795 --> 21:06.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
one of thousands of American
women and girls
forced into marriage each year.

21:06.799 --> 21:09.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN: I knew that I
wasn't going
to say no.

21:09.735 --> 21:10.803 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This was God's will.

21:10.836 --> 21:12.638 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
God had spoken.

21:12.671 --> 21:15.274 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it was just not even an
option.

21:15.307 --> 21:21.280 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I didn't think consciously in my
head I'm
being forced.

21:21.313 --> 21:25.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CRISTINA BICCHIERI, University
of Pennsylvania:
This is part of, if you will,
psychological

21:25.885 --> 21:27.686 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
manipulation.

21:27.720 --> 21:30.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Cristina
Bicchieri is
a professor of philosophy and
psychology at

21:30.823 --> 21:34.660 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the University of Pennsylvania
whose work
focuses on social norms.

21:34.693 --> 21:40.099 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
She says these marriage
practices are more
typical of close-knit,
conservative communities,

21:40.132 --> 21:42.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people with little contact to
the outside
world.

21:42.968 --> 21:50.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CRISTINA BICCHIERI: Your choices
are much
more restricted, and also it is
the case that

21:50.142 --> 21:58.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
even if the girl or the boy give
their consent,
it is force in the sense that
only they don't

21:58.150 --> 22:04.623 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
know or conceive of an
alternative, but it
is a terrifying thing to abandon
their community.

22:04.657 --> 22:05.624 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's scary.

22:05.658 --> 22:06.992 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Where do they go?

22:07.026 --> 22:08.994 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Whom do they talk to?

22:09.028 --> 22:14.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: For Nina
Van Harn, there
was no one and nowhere to go.

22:14.633 --> 22:16.535 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And then it was her wedding day.

22:16.569 --> 22:22.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN: I do remember
being very nervous,
and yet knowing that I needed to
be smiling,

22:22.741 --> 22:23.976 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and I was supposed to be happy.

22:24.009 --> 22:28.180 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I just looked in the mirror
and I thought,
this is it.

22:28.214 --> 22:32.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Nina's
husband wasn't
physically abusive, but
throughout over a

22:32.851 --> 22:38.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
decade marriage, she says that
she suffered
psychological abuse, under
severe pressure

22:38.090 --> 22:41.093 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
from her family and community.

22:41.126 --> 22:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every household chore, every
meal she cooked,
every family visit, even sexual
interaction,

22:47.366 --> 22:49.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
she said, came to feel like
imprisonment.

22:49.568 --> 23:00.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN: When you don't
consent willingly
to be with someone, then
acquiesce their requests,

23:00.112 --> 23:02.448 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it doesn't make it a yes.

23:02.481 --> 23:04.917 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It makes it, hey, I want to
survive today.

23:04.950 --> 23:09.822 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: An
attorney for her
husband after an initial
response to "PBS

23:09.855 --> 23:15.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NewsHour" didn't respond to
further inquiries,
and her father didn't respond to
multiple

23:15.160 --> 23:17.563 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
contact attempts.

23:17.596 --> 23:19.298 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Numbers are hard to come by.

23:19.331 --> 23:24.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But one recent study by a group
that works
against forced marriage found as
many 3,000

23:24.103 --> 23:25.871 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
cases in a two-year period.

23:25.904 --> 23:30.342 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Legally, marriage is between two
adults, age
18 years or older.

23:30.376 --> 23:33.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But every state in the country
allows for
exceptions.

23:33.846 --> 23:37.983 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Critics say these exceptions
endanger young
people, not help them.

23:38.017 --> 23:43.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Advocates say children as young
as 12 have
been married with the consent of
their parents,

23:43.055 --> 23:45.257 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
according to state data.

23:45.291 --> 23:50.329 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ten states also allow underage
girls to be
married if they become pregnant.

23:50.362 --> 23:55.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But critics point out that those
laws may
actually be used to legitimize
other crimes,

23:55.401 --> 23:58.203 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
such as rape.

23:58.237 --> 24:03.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a first-of-its-kind lawsuit,
Nina Van Harn
decided to sue the state of
Michigan for an

24:03.575 --> 24:08.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
annulment on the grounds that
her marriage
wasn't consensual, and was, in
fact, based

24:08.914 --> 24:10.516 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on compulsion.

24:10.549 --> 24:17.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With no legal precedent in the
matter, she
had to build the case from
scratch.

24:17.256 --> 24:22.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She left her husband and moved
to a nearby
city, where she now lives a much
less conservative

24:22.361 --> 24:23.429 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lifestyle.

24:23.462 --> 24:26.432 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The rest of her family ceased
all contact.

24:26.465 --> 24:31.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she and her former spouse
share joint
custody of their three children.

24:31.603 --> 24:34.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The case, she said, took on a
deep personal
significance.

24:34.807 --> 24:41.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN: I felt just a
sense that I
was going to actually not only
get away from

24:41.647 --> 24:44.216 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
him, but I was going to get
free.

24:44.249 --> 24:46.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: That's
what an annulment
meant to you?

24:46.985 --> 24:47.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
NINA VAN HARN: Uh-huh.

24:47.986 --> 24:48.954 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It meant freedom.

24:48.987 --> 24:51.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it meant a peace in my
conscience.

24:51.457 --> 24:55.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: When you
look at these
pictures, what goes through your
mind?

24:55.294 --> 24:59.231 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRAIDY REISS, Unchained at Last:
It's like
looking at a different person.

24:59.264 --> 25:00.999 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's like looking at a stranger.

25:01.033 --> 25:05.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Fraidy
Reiss felt similar
pressures in a very different
place.

25:05.070 --> 25:09.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She grew up in an ultra-orthodox
Jewish family
in Brooklyn, and she says that
the pressure

25:09.975 --> 25:13.846 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
she faced to get married was
obvious.

25:13.879 --> 25:19.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even though she was legally an
adult, 19 years
old, she said felt she had no
choice.

25:19.284 --> 25:22.855 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRAIDY REISS: You have never
been on a date
before.

25:22.888 --> 25:26.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And your whole life, you have
been told, you
need to get married right away.

25:26.558 --> 25:28.260 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You're terrified.

25:28.293 --> 25:31.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Reiss
Reiss was arranged
to marry a man whom she'd barely
met.

25:31.663 --> 25:36.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She remembers the ceremony as a
joyous time,
but she says her marriage took a
turn for

25:36.835 --> 25:38.170 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the worse.

25:38.203 --> 25:39.972 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRAIDY REISS: He would describe
to me how
he was going to kill me.

25:40.005 --> 25:41.640 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: In detail.

25:41.673 --> 25:43.442 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
FRAIDY REISS: In detail.

25:43.475 --> 25:45.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He would describe to me in
detail until my
-- he would explain how I was
going to take

25:45.844 --> 25:47.579 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
my last breath.

25:47.613 --> 25:50.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: The
threats prompted
Reiss to seek a restraining
order in a New

25:50.549 --> 25:55.754 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jersey state court, which was
granted in 2010,
and remains in force.

25:55.788 --> 26:02.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Divorce is considered sinful in
Reiss' community,
and family and friends offered
little sympathy.

26:02.161 --> 26:04.396 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On her own, she decided to take
action.

26:04.430 --> 26:08.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRAIDY REISS: My first plan was,
I'm just
going to get out of this
marriage, and then

26:09.001 --> 26:10.969 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it became, I'm going to get out
of this entire
situation.

26:11.003 --> 26:17.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Reiss left
the community,
and set out for what she
considered the unknown.

26:17.709 --> 26:23.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her family felt so betrayed, in
fact, that
they cut off all contact.

26:23.115 --> 26:27.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Professor Bicchieri says Reiss'
decision to
leave puts her in a rare
category.

26:27.319 --> 26:30.956 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CRISTINA BICCHIERI: Let's call
this woman
a trendsetter.

26:30.989 --> 26:38.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It will show to other women --
or it may not
be a woman -- can be a man, et
cetera -- that

26:38.130 --> 26:46.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it is possible to act against
the norm of
the community, is an example.

26:46.839 --> 26:48.640 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have more propensity to
risk.

26:48.674 --> 26:51.643 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They are more autonomous.

26:51.677 --> 27:00.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And another important element is
that they
must believe that their
rebelling in some

27:00.919 --> 27:04.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sense will be efficacious, that
they will
succeed.

27:04.289 --> 27:07.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Reiss
moved to New Jersey
with her two daughters.

27:07.993 --> 27:15.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her ex-husband retains some
visitation rights
to the girls.

27:15.167 --> 27:20.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Reiss started a nonprofit called
Unchained
at Last that lobbies to enact
tighter legislation

27:20.606 --> 27:23.442 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
addressing forced marriage
across the United
States.

27:23.475 --> 27:26.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRAIDY REISS: When people hear
about this,
they say, oh, well, that's just
happening

27:26.845 --> 27:30.649 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in this one religion, or that's
just happening
in this one immigrant community.

27:30.682 --> 27:32.885 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's a way to abdicate
responsibility.

27:32.918 --> 27:37.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's so important to raise
awareness about
this and to talk about this
publicly, because

27:37.723 --> 27:40.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you can't solve a problem that
nobody knows
exists.

27:40.993 --> 27:45.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Back in
Michigan, Nina
Van Harn and her lawyer, Matt
Burns, pushed

27:45.731 --> 27:47.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ahead with their legal battle.

27:47.766 --> 27:51.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The challenges, they say, are
not just legal,
but cultural.

27:51.436 --> 27:54.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATTHEW BURNS, Attorney for Nina
Van Harn:
The goal isn't to eradicate
arranged marriage.

27:54.873 --> 28:00.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In many cultures, that is the
norm, and it's
accepted, and -- but there's, I
think, a fine

28:00.913 --> 28:07.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
line and probably a fair gray
area between
what's arranged and what's
forced.

28:07.953 --> 28:12.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so that's, I think, another
difficulty
that we face here.

28:12.658 --> 28:17.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: While not
confronted
with physical abuse, Van Harn
overcame great

28:17.696 --> 28:20.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
psychological hurdles in
building her case.

28:20.332 --> 28:26.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN: When I walked
out, I didn't
just walk out on this person.

28:26.705 --> 28:28.640 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I walked out of my whole family.

28:28.674 --> 28:31.243 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I walked out of my community.

28:31.276 --> 28:35.814 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I walked out on many parts of
what had been
my faith.

28:35.847 --> 28:41.420 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I had to run very fast.

28:41.453 --> 28:43.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that was heart-wrenching
thing to do.

28:43.522 --> 28:50.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I did it because staying was
more frightening
than leaving.

28:50.929 --> 28:56.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: Now she
hopes that this
case will help other women from
all backgrounds

28:56.401 --> 28:58.904 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
escape similar situations.

28:58.937 --> 29:04.076 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, she has a steady job
in human resources
at an auto dealer.

29:04.109 --> 29:06.378 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She leads an active, busy
family.

29:06.411 --> 29:11.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And she has built a new group of
friends,
many of whom she met at a
support group sponsored

29:11.049 --> 29:12.618 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
by a local women's shelter.

29:12.651 --> 29:14.419 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
NINA VAN HARN: It's a community.

29:14.453 --> 29:18.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We are a community that works
together to
help each other through life.

29:18.657 --> 29:20.859 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We are, in some ways,
co-parents.

29:20.892 --> 29:22.628 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that's my family.

29:22.661 --> 29:25.097 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And they mean everything to me.

29:25.130 --> 29:32.170 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAYLE TZEMACH LEMMON: On August
1, Nina Van
Harn's husband agreed to annul
their marriage.

29:32.204 --> 29:38.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The end of this case, she hopes,
also will
mark a whole new a beginning for
her.

29:38.310 --> 29:42.180 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
