in some areas,
are being drowned out.

37:40.391 --> 37:42.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARLA HOLT, National Oceanic and
Atmospheric
Administration: People don't
really realize

37:42.527 --> 37:44.195 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
how noisy it is.

37:44.229 --> 37:46.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Sound travels very well
underwater compared
to air.

37:46.798 --> 37:49.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So it can travel very long
distances.

37:49.501 --> 37:54.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAT WISE: Marla Holt is a
wildlife biologist
for the National Oceanic and
Atmospheric Administration

37:54.539 --> 37:56.908 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Seattle.

37:56.941 --> 38:01.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
