have been studying
the impacts of noise pollution
on marine life

38:01.212 --> 38:03.014 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from big to small.

38:03.047 --> 38:07.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's been shown that noise can
cause behavior
changes, hearing loss, and it
can even be

38:07.218 --> 38:09.053 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
fatal.

38:09.087 --> 38:15.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Holt's research focuses on
orcas, also known
as killer whales, and how they
amplify their

38:15.260 --> 38:18.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
