noise.

38:34.612 --> 38:42.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: There's quite a
difference, and
you see it visually here too.

38:42.921 --> 38:46.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARLA HOLT: Yes, so, they really
have to pump
up the volume of their calls in
order to hear

38:46.891 --> 38:48.660 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
each other.

38:48.693 --> 38:52.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAT WISE: Many of the orcas Holt
studies spend
a lot of their time in
Washington state's

38:52.764 --> 38:54.465 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Puget Sound.

38:54.499 --> 38:57.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They and hundreds of other
marine species
have a lot more than just
container ships

38:57.735 --> 38:59.070 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to contend with.

38:59.103 --> 39:02.307 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
More than four million people
live around
the Sound.

39:02.340 --> 39:07.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The beautiful waterways of Puget
Sound are
what draw so many people to this
area, but

39:07.178 --> 39:11.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
all the boating and shoreline
development
make this a very noisy place to
be for marine

39:11.749 --> 39:13.451 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
life.

39:13.484 --> 39:16.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's an issue that the state of
Washington
has been trying to deal with for
quite some

39:16.321 --> 39:18.089 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
time.

39:18.122 --> 39:19.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
