it makes underwater
as it's being struck from above
the water,

39:47.552 --> 39:53.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and what that sound does to the
species that
are not only in the vicinity of
the pile,

39:53.825 --> 39:55.693 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but also miles and miles away.

39:55.727 --> 40:00.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAT WISE: While marine pile
driving is a relatively
small slice of the overall noise
pollution

40:00.999 --> 40:06.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
problem, it is one of the
loudest and most
distressful manmade noises for
marine life.

40:06.037 --> 40:11.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Documented fish kills around
marine pile driving
projects in the early 2000s led
to more state

40:11.142 --> 40:14.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and federal noise mitigation
requirements.

40:14.412 --> 40:18.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the main ways to reduce
the noise with
pile driving has been through
the use of bubble

40:18.449 --> 40:21.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
